half_duplex.translation: Half duplex mode for ESC telemetry

pin_swap.translation: Swap the TX and RX pins for the ESC telemetry

dyn_notch_q.translation: Quality factor of the notch filter.

gyro_soft_notch_cutoff_1.translation: Width of the notch filter in Hz.

gyro_soft_notch_cutoff_2.translation: Width of the notch filter in Hz.

rpm_min_hz.translation: Min frequency for the RPM filter.

gov_handover_throttle.english: Governor activates above this %. Below this the input throttle is passed to the ESC.
gov_handover_throttle.translation: Governor activates above this %. Under this the input throttle is passed to the ESC.

gov_recovery_time.english: Time constant for recovery spoolup, in seconds, measuring the time from zero to full headspeed.
gov_recovery_time.translation: Tid constant for recovery spoolup, in seconds, measuring the Tid from zero to Full Hodeturtall.

gov_spoolup_min_throttle.english: Minimum throttle to use for slow spoolup, in percent. For electric motors the default is 5%, for nitro this should be set so the clutch starts to engage for a smooth spoolup 10-15%.
gov_spoolup_min_throttle.translation: Min throttle to use for slow spoolup, in Prosent. For electric motors the default is 5%, for nitro this should be set so the clutch starts to engage for a smooth spoolup 10-15%.

gov_spoolup_time.english: Time constant for slow spoolup, in seconds, measuring the time from zero to full headspeed.
gov_spoolup_time.translation: Tid constant for slow spoolup, in seconds, measuring the Tid from zero to Full Hodeturtall.

gov_startup_time.english: Time constant for slow startup, in seconds, measuring the time from zero to full headspeed.
gov_startup_time.translation: Tid constant for slow startup, in seconds, measuring the Tid from zero to Full Hodeturtall.

gov_tracking_time.english: Time constant for headspeed changes, in seconds, measuring the time from zero to full headspeed.
gov_tracking_time.translation: Tid constant for Hodeturtall changes, in seconds, measuring the Tid from zero to Full Hodeturtall.

governor_collective_ff_weight.english: Collective precompensation weight - how much collective is mixed into the feedforward.
governor_collective_ff_weight.translation: Kollektiv precompensation weight - how much Kollektiv is mixed into the feedforward.

governor_cyclic_ff_weight.english: Cyclic precompensation weight - how much cyclic is mixed into the feedforward.
governor_cyclic_ff_weight.translation: Syklisk precompensation weight - how much Syklisk is mixed into the feedforward.

governor_headspeed.english: Target headspeed for the current profile.
governor_headspeed.translation: Target Hodeturtall for the current Profil.

governor_max_throttle.english: Maximum output throttle the governor is allowed to use.
governor_max_throttle.translation: Maks output throttle the Governor is allowed to use.

governor_min_throttle.english: Minimum output throttle the governor is allowed to use.
governor_min_throttle.translation: Min output throttle the Governor is allowed to use.

governor_tta_gain.english: TTA gain applied to increase headspeed to control the tail in the negative direction (e.g. motorised tail less than idle speed).
governor_tta_gain.translation: TTA gain applied to increase Hodeturtall to control the Hale in the negative direction (e.g. motorised Hale less than idle Fart).

governor_tta_limit.english: TTA max headspeed increase over full headspeed.
governor_tta_limit.translation: TTA Maks Hodeturtall increase over Full Hodeturtall.

governor_yaw_ff_weight.english: Yaw precompensation weight - how much yaw is mixed into the feedforward.
governor_yaw_ff_weight.translation: Yaw precompensation weight - how much yaw is mixed into the feedforward.

collective_tilt_correction_neg.english: Adjust the collective tilt correction scaling for negative collective pitch.
collective_tilt_correction_neg.translation: Adjust the Kollektiv tilt Korreksjon scaling for negative Kollektiv pitch.

collective_tilt_correction_pos.english: Adjust the collective tilt correction scaling for positive collective pitch.
collective_tilt_correction_pos.translation: Adjust the Kollektiv tilt Korreksjon scaling for positive Kollektiv pitch.

swash_geo_correction.english: Adjust if there is too much negative collective or too much positive collective.
swash_geo_correction.translation: Adjust if there is too much negative Kollektiv or too much positive Kollektiv.

swash_phase.english: Phase offset for the swashplate controls.
swash_phase.translation: Phase offset for the swashplate controls.

swash_pitch_limit.english: Maximum amount of combined cyclic and collective blade pitch.
swash_pitch_limit.translation: Maks amount of combined Syklisk and Kollektiv blade pitch.

swash_trim_0.english: Swash trim to level the swash plate when using fixed links.
swash_trim_0.translation: Swash trim to level the swash plate when using fixed links.

swash_trim_1.english: Swash trim to level the swash plate when using fixed links.
swash_trim_1.translation: Swash trim to level the swash plate when using fixed links.

swash_trim_2.english: Swash trim to level the swash plate when using fixed links.
swash_trim_2.translation: Swash trim to level the swash plate when using fixed links.

tail_center_trim.english: Sets tail rotor trim for 0 yaw for variable pitch, or tail motor throttle for 0 yaw for motorized.
tail_center_trim.translation: Sets Hale rotor trim for 0 yaw for variable pitch, or Hale Motor throttle for 0 yaw for motorized.

tail_motor_idle.english: Minimum throttle signal sent to the tail motor. This should be set just high enough that the motor does not stop.
tail_motor_idle.translation: Min throttle signal sent to the Hale Motor. This should be set just high enough that the Motor does not stop.

maxthrottle.english: This PWM value is sent to the ESC/Servo at full throttle
maxthrottle.translation: This PWM value is sent to the ESC/Servo at Full throttle

mincommand.english: This PWM value is sent when the motor is stopped
mincommand.translation: This PWM value is sent when the Motor is stopped

minthrottle.english: This PWM value is sent to the ESC/Servo at low throttle
minthrottle.translation: This PWM value is sent to the ESC/Servo at low throttle

motor_pole_count_0.english: The number of magnets on the motor bell.
motor_pole_count_0.translation: The number of magnets on the Motor bell.

motor_pwm_protocol.translation: The protocol Brukt to communicate with the ESC

motor_pwm_rate.translation: The frequency at which the ESC sends PWM signals to the Motor

angle_level_limit.english: Limit the maximum angle the helicopter will pitch/roll to while in Angle mode.
angle_level_limit.translation: Limit the Maks Vinkel the helicopter will pitch/roll to while in Vinkel mode.

angle_level_strength.english: Determines how aggressively the helicopter tilts back to level while in Angle Mode.
angle_level_strength.translation: Determines how aggressively the helicopter tilts Tilbake to level while in Vinkel Mode.

cyclic_cross_coupling_cutoff.english: Frequency limit for the compensation. Higher value will make the compensation action faster.
cyclic_cross_coupling_cutoff.translation: Frequency limit for the compensation. Higher value will make the compensation action faster.

cyclic_cross_coupling_gain.translation: Amount of compensation applied for pitch-to-roll decoupling.

cyclic_cross_coupling_ratio.english: Amount of roll-to-pitch compensation needed, vs. pitch-to-roll.
cyclic_cross_coupling_ratio.translation: Amount of roll-to-pitch compensation needed, vs. pitch-to-roll.

error_decay_limit_cyclic.english: Maximum bleed-off speed for cyclic I-term.
error_decay_limit_cyclic.translation: Maks bleed-Off Fart for Syklisk I-term.

error_decay_time_cyclic.translation: Tid constant for bleeding Off Syklisk I-term. Higher will stabilize hover, lower will drift.

error_decay_time_ground.english: Bleeds off the current controller error when the craft is not airborne to stop the craft tipping over.
error_decay_time_ground.translation: Bleeds Off the current controller Feil when the craft is not airborne to stop the craft tipping over.

error_limit_0.english: Hard limit for the angle error in the PID loop. The absolute error and thus the I-term will never go above these limits.
error_limit_0.translation: Hard limit for the Vinkel Feil in the PID loop. The absolute Feil and thus the I-term will never go above these Grenser.

error_limit_1.english: Hard limit for the angle error in the PID loop. The absolute error and thus the I-term will never go above these limits.
error_limit_1.translation: Hard limit for the Vinkel Feil in the PID loop. The absolute Feil and thus the I-term will never go above these Grenser.

error_limit_2.translation: Hard limit for the Vinkel Feil in the PID loop. The absolute Feil and thus the I-term will never go above these Grenser.

error_rotation.translation: Rotates the current roll and pitch Feil terms around yaw when the craft rotates. This is sometimes called Piro Compensation.

iterm_relax_cutoff_1.english: Helps reduce bounce back after fast stick movements. Can cause inconsistency in small stick movements if too low.

yaw_cyclic_ff_gain.translation: Syklisk feedforward mixed into yaw (Syklisk-to-yaw Precomp).

rc_arm_throttle.translation: Throttle must be at or Under this value in microseconds (us) to allow arming. Must be at least 10us lower than Min throttle.

rc_deadband.translation: Dodsonen for Syklisk control in microseconds (us).

channel_mode.translation: Select how each channel behaves when signal is lost: Auto, Hold, or Set.

channel_value.translation: Channel value used only when mode is Set.

accel_limit_1.translation: Maks Aks of the craft in response to a stick movement.

yaw_dynamic_ceiling_gain.translation: The Maks gain applied to the yaw dynamic ceiling.

yaw_dynamic_deadband_filter.translation: The Maks filter applied to the yaw dynamic deadband.

yaw_dynamic_deadband_gain.translation: The Maks gain applied to the yaw dynamic deadband.

rescue_climb_time.translation: Length of Tid the climb Kollektiv is applied before switching to hover.

rescue_exit_time.english: This limits rapid application of negative collective if the helicopter has rolled during rescue.
rescue_exit_time.translation: This Grenser rapid application of negative Kollektiv if the helicopter has rolled during rescue.

rescue_flip_gain.translation: Determine how aggressively the heli flips during inverted rescue.

rescue_flip_mode.translation: If rescue is activated while inverted, flip to upright - or remain inverted.

rescue_flip_time.translation: If the helicopter is in rescue and is trying to flip to upright and does not within this Tid, rescue will be aborted.

rescue_level_gain.translation: Determine how aggressively the heli levels during rescue.

rescue_max_setpoint_accel.translation: Limit how fast the helicopter accelerates into a roll/pitch. Larger helicopters may need slower Aks.

rescue_max_setpoint_rate.translation: Limit rescue roll/pitch rate. Larger helicopters may need slower Rotasjon rates.

rescue_pull_up_time.translation: When rescue is activated, helicopter will apply pull-up Kollektiv for this Tid period before moving to flip or climb stage.

always_fixed_1500_confirm.english: Always mode uses fixed 1500us. Set Min/Max to 1500us?
always_fixed_1500_confirm.translation: Always mode uses fixed 1500us. Set Min/Max to 1500us?

auto_detect_active_toggle.translation: Auto-detect active: toggle desired AUX channel

help_p3.english: Gyro notch filters: Use for filtering specific frequency ranges. Typically not needed in most helis.
help_p3.translation: Gyro notch filters: Use for filtering specific frequency ranges. Typically not needed in most helis.

help_p4.english: Dynamic Notch Filters: Automatically creates notch filters within the min and max frequency range.
help_p4.translation: Dynamic Notch Filters: Automatically creates notch filters within the min and Maks frequency range.

start_prompt.english: Would you like to start the test? Choose the test run time below.
start_prompt.translation: Would you like to Start the test? Choose the test run Tid Under.

help_p1.english: FeedForward (Roll/Pitch): Start at 70, increase until stops are sharp with no drift. Keep roll and pitch equal.
help_p1.translation: FeedForward (Roll/Pitch): Start at 70, increase until stops are sharp with no drift. Keep roll and pitch equal.

help_p2.english: I Gain (Roll/Pitch): Raise gradually for stable piro pitch pumps. Too high causes wobbles; match roll/pitch values.
help_p2.translation: I Gain (Roll/Pitch): Raise gradually for stable piro pitch pumps. Too high causes wobbles; match roll/pitch values.

help_p3.english: Tail P/I/D Gains: Increase P until slight wobble in funnels, then back off slightly. Raise I until tail holds firm in hard moves (too high causes slow wag). Adjust D for smooth stops-higher for slow servos, lower for fast ones.
help_p3.translation: Hale P/I/D Gevinst: Increase P until slight wobble in funnels, then Tilbake Off slightly. Raise I until Hale holds firm in hard moves (too high causes slow wag). Adjust D for smooth stops-higher for slow servos, lower for fast ones.

help_p4.english: Test & Adjust: Fly, observe, and fine-tune for best performance in real conditions.
help_p4.translation: Test & Adjust: Fly, observe, and fine-tune for best Ytelse in real conditions.

help_p1.english: The battery settings are used to configure the flight controller to monitor the battery voltage and provide warnings when the voltage drops below a certain level.
help_p1.translation: The battery Innstill are Brukt to configure the flight controller to monitor the battery voltage and provide warnings when the voltage drops Under a certain level.

no_ports_reported.english: No serial ports reported by FC.
no_ports_reported.translation: No serial ports reported by FC.

help_p1.english: Acro Trainer: How aggressively the heli tilts back to level when flying in Acro Trainer Mode.
help_p1.translation: Acro Trainer: How aggressively the heli tilts Tilbake to level when flying in Acro Trainer Mode.

help_p2.english: Angle Mode: How aggressively the heli tilts back to level when flying in Angle Mode.
help_p2.translation: Vinkel Mode: How aggressively the heli tilts Tilbake to level when flying in Vinkel Mode.

help_p3.english: Horizon Mode: How aggressively the heli tilts back to level when flying in Horizon Mode.
help_p3.translation: Horizon Mode: How aggressively the heli tilts Tilbake to level when flying in Horizon Mode.

help_p1.english: Full headspeed: Headspeed target when at 100% throttle input.
help_p1.translation: Fullt hodeturtall: Hodeturtall target when at 100% throttle input.

help_p2.english: PID master gain: How hard the governor works to hold the RPM.
help_p2.translation: PID master gain: How hard the Governor works to hold the RPM.

help_p3.english: Gains: Fine tuning of the governor.
help_p3.translation: Gevinst: Fine tuning of the Governor.

help_p4.english: Precomp: Governor precomp gain for yaw, cyclic, and collective inputs.
help_p4.translation: Precomp: Governor Precomp gain for yaw, Syklisk, and Kollektiv inputs.

help_p5.english: Max throttle: The maximum throttle % the governor is allowed to use.
help_p5.translation: Maks throttle: The Maks throttle % the Governor is allowed to use.

help_p6.english: Tail Torque Assist: For motorized tails. Gain and limit of headspeed increase when using main rotor torque for yaw assist.
help_p6.translation: Hale moment hjelp: For motorized tails. Gain and limit of Hodeturtall increase when using Hoved rotor Moment for yaw Hjelp.

help_p1.english: Collective Pitch Compensation: Increasing will compensate for the pitching motion caused by tail drag when climbing.
help_p1.translation: Kollektiv Pitch Compensation: Increasing will compensate for the pitching motion caused by Hale drag when climbing.

help_p2.english: Cross Coupling Gain: Removes roll coupling when only elevator is applied.
help_p2.translation: Cross Coupling Gain: Removes roll coupling when only elevator is applied.

help_p3.english: Cross Coupling Ratio: Amount of compensation (pitch vs roll) to apply.
help_p3.translation: Cross Coupling Forhold: Amount of compensation (pitch vs roll) to apply.

help_p4.english: Cross Coupling Freq. Limit: Frequency limit for the compensation, higher value will make the compensation action faster.
help_p4.translation: Cross Coupling Freq. Limit: Frequency limit for the compensation, higher value will make the compensation action faster.

help_p1.english: PID Bandwidth: Overall bandwidth in HZ used by the PID loop.
help_p1.translation: PID Bandwidth: Overall bandwidth in HZ Brukt by the PID loop.

help_p2.english: D-term cutoff: D-term cutoff frequency in HZ.
help_p2.translation: D-term cutoff: D-term cutoff frequency in HZ.

help_p3.english: B-term cutoff: B-term cutoff frequency in HZ.
help_p3.translation: B-term cutoff: B-term cutoff frequency in HZ.

help_p1.english: Error decay ground: PID decay to help prevent heli from tipping over when on the ground.
help_p1.translation: Feil Demping Bakke: PID Demping to Hjelp prevent heli from tipping over when on the Bakke.

help_p2.english: Error limit: Angle limit for I-term.
help_p2.translation: Feil limit: Vinkel limit for I-term.

help_p3.english: Offset limit: Angle limit for High Speed Integral (O-term).
help_p3.translation: Offset limit: Vinkel limit for High Fart Integral (O-term).

help_p4.english: Error rotation: Allow errors to be shared between all axes.
help_p4.translation: Feil Rotasjon: Allow errors to be shared between all axes.

help_p5.english: I-term relax: Limit accumulation of I-term during fast movements - helps reduce bounce back after fast stick movements. Generally needs to be lower for large helis and can be higher for small helis. Best to only reduce as much as is needed for your flying style.
help_p5.translation: I-term relax: Limit accumulation of I-term during fast movements - helps reduce bounce Tilbake after fast stick movements. Generally needs to be lower for large helis and can be higher for small helis. Best to only reduce as much as is needed for your flying style.

help_p1.english: Flip to upright: Flip the heli upright when rescue is activated.
help_p1.translation: Flip to upright: Flip the heli upright when rescue is activated.

help_p2.english: Pull-up: How much collective and for how long to arrest the fall.
help_p2.translation: Pull-up: How much Kollektiv and for how long to arrest the fall.

help_p3.english: Climb: How much collective to maintain a steady climb - and how long.
help_p3.translation: Climb: How much Kollektiv to maintain a steady climb - and how long.

help_p4.english: Hover: How much collective to maintain a steady hover.
help_p4.translation: Hover: How much Kollektiv to maintain a steady hover.

help_p5.english: Flip: How long to wait before aborting because the flip did not work.
help_p5.translation: Flip: How long to wait before aborting because the flip did not work.

help_p6.english: Gains: How hard to fight to keep heli level when engaging rescue mode.
help_p6.translation: Gevinst: How hard to fight to keep heli level when engaging rescue mode.

help_p7.english: Rate and Accel: Max rotation and acceleration rates when leveling during rescue.
help_p7.translation: Rate and Accel: Maks Rotasjon and Aks rates when leveling during rescue.

help_p1.english: Set the current flight profile or rate profile you would like to use.
help_p1.translation: Set the current flight Profil or rate Profil you would like to use.

help_p2.translation: If you use a switch on your radio to change flight or rate modes, this will override this choice as soon as you toggle the switch.

save_prompt.english: Save current page to flight controller?
save_prompt.translation: Lagre current page to flight controller?

help_p1.english: Yaw Stop Gain: Higher stop gain will make the tail stop more aggressively but may cause oscillations if too high. Adjust CW or CCW to make the yaw stops even.
help_p1.translation: Yaw Stop Gain: Higher stop gain will make the Hale stop more aggressively but may cause oscillations if too high. Adjust CW or CCW to make the yaw stops even.

help_p2.english: Precomp Cutoff: Frequency limit for all yaw precompensation actions.
help_p2.translation: Precomp Cutoff: Frequency limit for all yaw precompensation actions.

help_p3.english: Cyclic FF Gain: Tail precompensation for cyclic inputs.
help_p3.translation: Syklisk FF Gain: Hale precompensation for Syklisk inputs.

help_p4.english: Collective FF Gain: Tail precompensation for collective inputs.
help_p4.translation: Kollektiv FF Gain: Hale precompensation for Kollektiv inputs.

help_p5.english: Collective Impulse FF: Impulse tail precompensation for collective inputs. If you need extra tail precompensation at the beginning of collective input.
help_p5.translation: Kollektiv Impuls FF: Impuls Hale precompensation for Kollektiv inputs. If you need extra Hale precompensation at the beginning of Kollektiv input.

help_p1.english: Configure your radio settings. Stick center, arm, throttle hold, and throttle cut.
help_p1.translation: Configure your radio Innstill. Stick Senter, arm, throttle hold, and throttle cut.

help_default_p1.english: Default: We keep this to make button appear for rates.
help_default_p1.translation: Default: We keep this to make button appear for rates.

help_default_p2.english: We will use the sub keys below.
help_default_p2.translation: We will use the sub keys Under.

help_table_0_p1.english: All values are set to zero because no RATE TABLE is in use.
help_table_0_p1.translation: All values are set to zero because no RATE TABLE is in use.

help_table_1_p1.english: RC Rate: Maximum rotation rate at full stick deflection.
help_table_1_p1.translation: RC Rate: Maks Rotasjon rate at Full stick deflection.

help_table_1_p2.english: SuperRate: Increases maximum rotation rate while reducing sensitivity around half stick.
help_table_1_p2.translation: SuperRate: Increases Maks Rotasjon rate while reducing sensitivity around half stick.

help_table_1_p3.english: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's center where fine controls are needed.
help_table_1_p3.translation: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's Senter where fine controls are needed.

help_table_2_p1.english: Rate: Maximum rotation rate at full stick deflection in degrees per second.
help_table_2_p1.translation: Rate: Maks Rotasjon rate at Full stick deflection in degrees per second.

help_table_2_p2.english: Acro+: Increases the maximum rotation rate while reducing sensitivity around half stick.
help_table_2_p2.translation: Acro+: Increases the Maks Rotasjon rate while reducing sensitivity around half stick.

help_table_2_p3.english: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's center where fine controls are needed.
help_table_2_p3.translation: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's Senter where fine controls are needed.

help_table_3_p1.english: RC Rate: Maximum rotation rate at full stick deflection.
help_table_3_p1.translation: RC Rate: Maks Rotasjon rate at Full stick deflection.

help_table_3_p2.english: Rate: Increases maximum rotation rate while reducing sensitivity around half stick.
help_table_3_p2.translation: Rate: Increases Maks Rotasjon rate while reducing sensitivity around half stick.

help_table_3_p3.english: RC Curve: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's center where fine controls are needed.
help_table_3_p3.translation: RC Curve: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's Senter where fine controls are needed.

help_table_4_p1.english: Center Sensitivity: Use to reduce sensitivity around center stick. Set Center Sensitivity to the same as Max Rate for a linear response. A lower number than Max Rate will reduce sensitivity around center stick. Note that higher than Max Rate will increase the Max Rate - not recommended as it causes issues in the Blackbox log.
help_table_4_p1.translation: Senter Sensitivity: Use to reduce sensitivity around Senter stick. Set Senter Sensitivity to the same as Maks Rate for a linear response. A lower number than Maks Rate will reduce sensitivity around Senter stick. Note that higher than Maks Rate will increase the Maks Rate - not recommended as it causes issues in the Blackbox log.

help_table_4_p2.english: Max Rate: Maximum rotation rate at full stick deflection in degrees per second.
help_table_4_p2.translation: Maks Rate: Maks Rotasjon rate at Full stick deflection in degrees per second.

help_table_4_p3.english: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's center where fine controls are needed.
help_table_4_p3.translation: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's Senter where fine controls are needed.

help_table_5_p1.english: RC Rate: Use to reduce sensitivity around center stick. RC Rate set to one half of the Max Rate is linear. A lower number will reduce sensitivity around center stick. Higher than one half of the Max Rate will also increase the Max Rate.
help_table_5_p1.translation: RC Rate: Use to reduce sensitivity around Senter stick. RC Rate set to one half of the Maks Rate is linear. A lower number will reduce sensitivity around Senter stick. Higher than one half of the Maks Rate will also increase the Maks Rate.

help_table_5_p2.english: Max Rate: Maximum rotation rate at full stick deflection in degrees per second.
help_table_5_p2.translation: Maks Rate: Maks Rotasjon rate at Full stick deflection in degrees per second.

help_table_5_p3.english: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's center where fine controls are needed.
help_table_5_p3.translation: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's Senter where fine controls are needed.

help_table_6_p1.english: Rate: Maximum rotation rate at full stick deflection in degrees per second.
help_table_6_p1.translation: Rate: Maks Rotasjon rate at Full stick deflection in degrees per second.

help_table_6_p2.english: Shape: Shifts the vertex of the control curve. Up to this point, the signal translation is linear. This defines how far the stick travel remains proportional before the curve becomes progressive.
help_table_6_p2.translation: Shape: Shifts the vertex of the control curve. Up to this point, the signal translation is linear. This defines how far the stick travel remains proportional before the curve becomes progressive.

help_table_6_p3.english: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's center where fine controls are needed.
help_table_6_p3.translation: Expo: Reduces sensitivity near the stick's Senter where fine controls are needed.

help_p1.english: Rates type: Choose the rate type you prefer flying with. Raceflight and Actual are the most straightforward.
help_p1.translation: Rates type: Choose the rate type you prefer flying with. Raceflight and Actual are the most straightforward.

help_p2.english: Dynamics: Applied regardless of rates type. Typically left on defaults but can be adjusted to smooth heli movements, like with scale helis.
help_p2.translation: Dynamics: Applied regardless of rates type. Typically left on defaults but can be adjusted to smooth heli movements, like with scale helis.

msg_reset_to_defaults.translation: Rate type changed. Values will be reset to defaults.

enable_servo_override_msg.translation: Servo override allows you to 'trim' your servo Senter point in real Tid.

help_default_p1.translation: Please Velg the servo you would like to configure from the list Under.

help_default_p2.translation: Primary flight controls that use the rotorflight mixer will display in the section called 'mixer'.

help_fields_flags.translation: 0 = Default, 1=Reverse, 2 = Geo Korreksjon, 3 = Reverse + Geo Korreksjon

help_tool_p1.english: Override: [*] Enable override to allow real-time updates of servo center point.
help_tool_p1.translation: Override: [*] Enable override to allow real-Tid updates of servo Senter point.

help_tool_p2.english: Center: Adjust the center position of the servo.
help_tool_p2.translation: Senter: Adjust the Senter position of the servo.

help_tool_p3.english: Minimum/Maximum: Adjust the end points of the selected servo.
help_tool_p3.translation: Min/Maks: Adjust the end points of the selected servo.

help_tool_p4.english: Scale: Adjust the amount the servo moves for a given input.
help_tool_p4.translation: Scale: Adjust the amount the servo moves for a given input.

help_tool_p5.english: Rate: The frequency the servo runs best at - check with manufacturer.
help_tool_p5.translation: Rate: The frequency the servo runs best at - check with manufacturer.

help_tool_p6.english: Speed: The speed the servo moves. Generally only used for the cyclic servos to help the swash move evenly. Optional - leave all at 0 if unsure.
help_tool_p6.translation: Fart: The Fart the servo moves. Generally only Brukt for the Syklisk servos to Hjelp the swash move evenly. Valgfri - leave all at 0 if unsure.
